  "prompt": "What is the legal framework surrounding money laundering?",
  "response": "The legal framework surrounding money laundering typically encompasses several key elements:\n\n1. International Regulations\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- United Nations Convention Against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Basel Committee guidelines\n\n2. National Legislation\n- Anti-Money Laundering (AML) laws\n- Bank Secrecy Act\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) requirements\n- Suspicious Activity Reporting (SAR) obligations\n\n3. Key Legal Provisions\n- Criminalizing money laundering activities\n- Establishing reporting requirements for financial institutions\n- Defining predicate offenses\n- Setting penalties for non-compliance\n\n4. Regulatory Compliance\n- Customer due diligence\n- Transaction monitoring\n- Record-keeping requirements\n- Reporting suspicious transactions\n\n5. Enforcement Mechanisms\n- Financial intelligence units\n- Law enforcement investigations\n- Asset seizure and forfeiture\n- Criminal prosecution\n\n6. Institutional Responsibilities\n- Banks\n- Credit institutions\n- Money transfer services\n- Cryptocurrency exchanges\n\n7. International Cooperation\n- Information sharing between jurisdictions\n- Extradition agreements\n- Mutual legal assistance treaties\n\nThese frameworks aim to prevent, detect, and prosecute financial crimes.",
